You are working on the CodeFlare SDK, a Python SDK for batch resource management on Kubernetes.

Read AGENTS.md at the project root for full instructions. Key points:

- Python ^3.11, Poetry for dependency management (never pip install)
- Run `black` on changed files before committing
- Maintain >= 90% test coverage
- Do NOT modify anything under src/codeflare_sdk/vendored/
- Use type hints on all function signatures and return types
- Use dataclasses for structured data, Enums for state values
- Use relative imports within the codeflare_sdk package
- Place unit tests alongside source: src/codeflare_sdk/<module>/test_<name>.py
- The conftest.py at src/codeflare_sdk/conftest.py auto-mocks K8s API clients
- Never make real Kubernetes API calls in unit tests
- Export new public classes/functions in src/codeflare_sdk/__init__.py
- Use _kube_api_error_handling() for Kubernetes API errors
- User-friendly error messages (SDK targets data scientists)

Quick commands:
  poetry install --with test,dev
  pytest -v src/codeflare_sdk
  black <file>
